   <Row ss:Height="165">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">CSE 472</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Numerical Methods</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">13.04.2026</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">In this course, numerical representation, rounding and truncation errors, Taylor series, convergence rate, condition number, and stability are discussed to provide the theoretical foundation for the accuracy and reliability of numerical methods. For nonlinear equations, root-finding methods such as bracketing, bisection, Newton, and secant methods are introduced, and their convergence behavior is compared. For systems of linear equations, Gaussian elimination with pivoting, LU/Cholesky factorizations, sparse and structured matrices, and iterative methods such as Jacobi, Gauss–Seidel, and Conjugate Gradient are studied; in addition, least-squares problems are introduced via QR and singular value decomposition (SVD). For approximating data sets, polynomial interpolation, Lagrange and Newton polynomials, as well as piecewise polynomials and spline-based methods are briefly covered. For definite integrals, basic numerical integration techniques and the Monte Carlo approach are presented, while for ordinary differential equations, numerical solution techniques are introduced with an emphasis on Runge–Kutta methods.</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=447514&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="105">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 012</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Epigenetics</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Epigenetic concepts and the questions it tries to define, DNA packaging, histones and histone modifications, Epigenetic mechanisms, Inheritance of epigenetic mechanisms, Epigenetic silencing and ncRNA in epigenetic silencing, Relationship between histone modifications and DNA methylation, Relationship between human diseases and epigenetic changes, Epigenetics phenomena and interactions, epigenetic reprogramming and development, pluripotency and preservation and differentiation of embryonic stem cells, the concept of epigenetic therapy, Epigenetic studies, methods and databases used in epigenetic studies, Epigenetic analysis methods.</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412015&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="45">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 013</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Developmental Biology</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Developmental biology: the formation of three main lineages starting from fertilization, followed by the formation of organs developing from these developmental layers, is explained from the perspective of molecular biology within the framework of embryogenesis.</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412016&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="90">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">MBG 014</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Proteoimics</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">24.06.2025</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">General Properties of Proteins: Structure and function of proteins, Overview of proteomic concepts, Transition from Genomics to Proteomics: Functional genomics at DNA and RNA level, Separation techniques used in proteomic analysis, Techniques used in protein identification, Use of mass spectrometry, Use of standard two-dimensional gel electrophoresis, Quantitative analysis in proteomics , Clinical proteomics, Structural proteomics, Proteomics in personalized drug development, Proteomics applications in cancer, Reasons of rapid progress in proteomics studies, Bioinformatics in proteomics.</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=412017&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
   </Row>
