    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">English Language Course for Erasmus I</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Reading Skill-At the end of this course, students will be able to • read for/understand specific information, main ideas, gist and opinions • Use pre-reading skills to activate schemata and predict content of advanced texts • identify the common types of support in arguments, their relevance and irrelevance, common argument flaws, opposing points of views and refutations • expand targeted vocabulary</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Discussion Vocabulary Study</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Complete IELTS Cambridge</Data></Cell>
