   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="45">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Active membranes basics (E &amp; S) 3 periods {Readings: Rinzel &amp; Ermentrout Chap. 5 K&amp;S; Chap. 4 B&amp; B; handouts} Phase plane analysis of properties Hard copy of the revised chapter and the figures Channeling with Bard space clamped HH type propagation of action potentials repetitive firing stimulating active membranes thresholds, entrainment Simulation of active membrane</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="30">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Computer simulation of activity (Handout, Chap. 12 B&amp;B) simple HH channel Detailed presentation of specific models Traub McCormicks thalamocortical cell Tutorial on McCormick/Huguenard models Try the voltage clamp without the fishy smell</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="45">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">8</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Synapses 2 periods {Readings: Chap. 6,McCormick Chap.2 in Shepherd 1990} Channels model basics ion gated voltage gated Kinetic theory (Mainen and Sejnowski) GABA_A vs GABA_B second messengers Multiple levels of simulation Numeric approximation Simulating channel effects Example models Brown, others</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="45">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">9</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Population modeling (S) 2 periods { Readings Wilson &amp; Bower Chap. 9 K&amp;S; Chap. 17 B&amp;B; Chap. 3&amp;4 White; Douglas &amp; Martin 1992) } Please grab this lengthy paper for the next several lectures. Simplifying systems specialization receptive fields columns regions laminar distribution Identifying cell types Building up the system Interconnecting cells Examining population behavior</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="30">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">10</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Simplified biological modeling Population activity in barrel fields (Dan Simons) 1 period using biological input and outputs problems of scaling how much and what kind of detail</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
   <Row ss:Height="60">
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Bilgisayar Mühendisliği (İngilizce)</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">6246</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">BME 517</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Mathematical Basis of Computational Neuroscience</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">11</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">Connectionist modeling with a biological interest (Jay McClelland David Plaut) 5 periods Introduction to PDP: philosophy, framework learning rules: Hebb, comp. learn, contrast Hebb, BP relation biological synaptic modification Perception and models of perception/attentional disorders interactive activation model, stochastic version relation to Zipser's work relating network to neural variables Mosher &amp; Behrmann and other models of neglect and other phenomena</Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
    <Cell ss:StyleID="s63"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=411841&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
   </Row>
